## Architecture

```
User: "I want feature X"
         ↓
   ┌──────────┐  specs    ┌──────────┐  dispatch   ┌──────────┐
   │    BA    │ ────────▶ │ DEV Lead │ ──────────▶ │ DEV-BE   │
   │ (specs)  │           │(beads +  │             │ DEV-FE   │
   └──────────┘           │ dispatch)│             └──────────┘
                          └──────────┘                  ↓
                                                  ┌──────────┐
                                                  │ TESTER   │
                                                  └──────────┘
                                                       ↓
                                                  ┌──────────┐
                                                  │ DEVOPS   │
                                                  └──────────┘
```

## Subagents

Defined in `.claude/agents/`:

| Agent | File | Role | Model |
|-------|------|------|-------|
| `ba` | `ba.md` | Gather requirements, create specs | Opus |
| `dev-lead` | `dev-lead.md` | Sync specs → Beads, label tasks, dispatch | Sonnet |
| `dev-be` | `dev-be.md` | Backend tasks | Sonnet |
| `dev-fe` | `dev-fe.md` | Frontend tasks | Sonnet |
| `tester` | `tester.md` | Validate completed work | Sonnet |
| `devops` | `devops.md` | PRs, Beads sync | Sonnet |

## Commands

| Command | Purpose |
|---------|---------|
| `/opsx:feature` | Full pipeline: BA → DEV Lead → DEV → TESTER → DEVOPS |
| `/opsx:propose` | Create specs only (BA) |
| `/opsx:sync` | Sync specs to Beads (DEV Lead) |
| `/opsx:status` | View combined progress |

## Rules

- Beads is the source of truth for task status
- Task descriptions in Beads must be self-contained
- One branch per task: `agent/<bead-id>-<short-desc>`
- Always run TESTER before merge
- 1 DEV agent at a time

## Beads Commands

```bash
bd ready                          # Unblocked tasks
bd show <id>                      # Task details
bd update <id> --claim            # Claim a task
bd close <id> -r "Done"           # Complete a task
bd graph --all                    # Dependency graph
bd memories                       # Show long memories
bd remember "insight" --key name  # Save memory
```
